title: Working the land but rarely owning it: life for New Zealand’s young farmers
summary: A nation reliant on agriculture is experiencing a decline in the number of farms, impacting its agricultural landscape. Young individuals are finding it increasingly difficult to purchase land, contributing to this trend. This shift signals significant changes in the sector's sustainability and future viability.
